A former Minister of Information, Chief Alex Akinyele, is dead. A statement by one of his sons, Constantine Akinfolarin Akinyele, confirmed that the Ondo chief passed away late Thursday night after a brief illness. He served as the Minister of Information, then later became Chairman of the National Sports Commission (NSC). And it was under his watch as NSC Chairman that Nigeria qualified for their first ever World Cup finals after drawing with the Desert Warriors of Algeria in the final qualifier for USAâ€™94. 